x4freetext: low levels of 236U and 239Pu were pressed into
pellets (6 mm in diam., ~0.2 mm thick) for four
- IRMM-a (50.0 mg) for kT~25 keV irradiation,
- IRMM-3 (45.9 mg) for thermal neutron irradiation,
- IRMM-4 (40.9 mg) for thermal neutron irradiation.
The thermal neutron irradiations with a cold neutron
beam at the Budapest Neutron Centre are to verify
Irradiated for 7 days (kT~25 keV) and 12 days
(<En>=426 keV) as well as 5 and 8 days for cold
Pu was separated from uranium bulk material.
Known amount of spikes of 233U (IRMM-058) and 242Pu
(IRMM-085) was added to trace U and Pu separation.
About 30 AMS samples per pellet were analyzed at
Ep=1912 keV on LiF (20 um thick) for kT~25 keV,
Ep=2285 keV on LiF (5 um thick) for <En>=426 keV.
